Write an algorithm that someone could use to check if they have reached their
savings target and also print the amount of excess money they have saved.
The loop starts at ‘do’ and ends when the
‘until’ condition is true — when the total
is greater than or equal to the target.
The loop starts by checking the ‘while’ condition is
true and keeps repeating until it is false — when
the total is greater than or equal to the target.
Both of these loops work exactly the same when target > 0.
If the target is 0, the WHILE loop won’t expect funds to be input, whereas the DO UNTIL loop will.
You could use either of the loops shown above — the code before and after the loop is exactly the same.
